meanings.definition: To surpass in rate or speed.
meanings.sent1: The cheetah can outrate any other animal in a race.
meanings.sent2: The new sports car can easily outrate the old model in speed.
meanings.sent3: It's funny how the tortoise managed to outrate the hare in the race.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outrate her competitors was like a speeding bullet.
meanings.sent5: The rocket's speed outrated anything ever seen before.

meanings.sent1: The floodwaters outrate the capacity of the drainage system.
meanings.sent2: The demand for the product may outrate the supply during the holiday season.
meanings.sent3: The balloon's size managed to outrate the expectations of the party guests.
meanings.sent4: Her excitement outrated her ability to stay calm.
meanings.sent5: The tree's growth outrated the space available in the garden.

meanings.sent1: His kindness can outrate his occasional grumpiness.
meanings.sent2: The final bill may outrate the initial estimate due to additional charges.
meanings.sent3: The number of balloons used for decoration managed to outrate the number of guests.
meanings.sent4: Her love for animals outrated her fear of spiders.
meanings.sent5: The beauty of the sunset outrated any painting he had ever seen.
